section.section:
A restitution obligor immediately shall notify the court, the Central Collection Unit, and the Division or Department of Juvenile Services of:
any objection to an earnings withholding order;
the current home address of the restitution obligor;
the name of the employer;
the work address of the restitution obligor; and
any change of employer, home address, or work address of the restitution obligor.

An employer who is served with an earnings withholding order under this section immediately shall notify the court, the Central Collection Unit, and the Division or Department of Juvenile Services of:
any justification for the employer's inability to comply with the earnings withholding order;
the home address of the restitution obligor on the termination of employment;
information regarding the new place of employment of the restitution obligor; or
the employer's reemployment of the restitution obligor.
